<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="miscellaneous" id="idbcadf13f-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Extension of Program</heading><p><ref href="/us/pl/119/4/dA/tVII/s1709">Pub. L. 119–4, div. A, title VII, § 1709</ref>, <date date="2025-03-15">Mar. 15, 2025</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/139/29">139 Stat. 29</ref>, provided that:<quotedContent origin="/us/pl/119/4/dA/tVII/s1709">
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0"><num value="a">“(a)</num><content> Sections 1309(a) and 1319 of the National Flood Insurance Act of 1968 (<ref href="/us/usc/t42/s4016/a">42 U.S.C. 4016(a)</ref> and 4026) shall be applied by substituting the date specified in section 1106 of this Act [<date date="2025-09-30">Sept. 30, 2025</date>] for ‘<date date="2023-09-30">September 30, 2023</date>’.</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0"><num value="b">“(b)</num><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> Subject to paragraph (2), this section shall become effective immediately upon enactment of this Act [div. A of <ref href="/us/pl/119/4">Pub. L. 119–4</ref>, approved <date date="2025-03-15">Mar. 15, 2025</date>].</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0"><num value="2">“(2)</num><content> If this Act is enacted after <date date="2025-03-14">March 14, 2025</date>, this section shall be applied as if it were in effect on <date date="2025-03-14">March 14, 2025</date>.”</content>
</paragraph>
</subsection>
</quotedContent>
</p>
